# HR Portal Agent System

You are working on a multi-tenant HR Portal modular monolith. Follow the agent system in `/cursor/`.

## Before any task

1. Read relevant files in `/cursor/core/` (rules, TDD, guardrails, architecture, patterns)
2. Check `/cursor/tasks/` for the current execution plan and task status
3. Use `/cursor/memory/` as source of truth — never invent domain entities or API endpoints
4. Validate work against `/cursor/evals/` before marking complete

## Non-negotiables

- Clean Architecture: Api → Application → Domain → Infrastructure
- Controllers thin; business logic in Application/Domain only
- All dependencies via interfaces; no hardcoded secrets
- Multi-tenancy mandatory — `ITenantEntity` + global query filters
- Services return `Result<T>`; map to HTTP in controllers
- No feature complete without tests (`dotnet test` / frontend build)
- Update `/cursor/memory/` when domain model or API contracts change

## Reference

- Canonical backend module: `HrPortal.Employees`
- Master prompt: `/cursor/prompts/00_master_prompt.md`
- Architecture decisions: `/cursor/memory/architecture_decisions.md`
